dlinkSwNetworkAccessAuthMIB.name: dlinkSwNetworkAccessAuthMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file for 'Network Access Authentication.' functionality.

dlinkSwNetworkAccessAuthMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwNetworkAccessAuthMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for Network Access Authentication in the system. Network Access Authentication provides generic configurations for authentication methods in the system and manages the failover sequence of these methods in a flexible manner.

DlinkAuthMethod.name: DlinkAuthMethod
DlinkAuthMethod.description: The authentication methods and protocols supported in Network Access Authentication. other : other methods no defined here. 'other' is a read-only value and cannot be used in set operation. dot1x : 802.1X Protocol. macAuth : MAC-based Access Control. webAuth : Web-based Access Control. jwac : Japanese Web Authentication.

DlinkAuthMethodList.name: DlinkAuthMethodList
DlinkAuthMethodList.description: The authentication methods being used by Network Access Authentication. This object is a bit map, with each bit representing a different authentication type as identified below. A 1-bit indicates the authentication method is used. A 0-bit indicates the authentication method is not used. dot1x : 802.1X Protocol. macAuth : MAC-based Access Control. webAuth : Web-based Access Control. jwac : Japanese Web Authentication.

DlinkAuthHostMode.name: DlinkAuthHostMode
DlinkAuthHostMode.description: The authentication mode of a controlled port. multiHost : If a port is operated in multi-host mode, once a host is authenticated, all remaining hosts are also authenticated in a single domain. multiAuth : If a port is operated in multi-auth mode, each host is authenticated separately in a single domain.

DlinkCompAuthMode.name: DlinkCompAuthMode
DlinkCompAuthMode.description: The compound authentication mode of a controlled port. any : The host needs pass one of the authentication methods (802.1X, MAC-based Access Control, WAC and JWAC). macJwac : MAC-based Access Control will be verified first. If a client passed MAC authentication, JWAC will be verified. The host needs pass both authentication methods. macWac : MAC-based Access Control will be verified first. If a client passed MAC authentication, WAC will be verified. The host needs pass both authentication methods.

dnaMacMoveMode.name: dnaMacMoveMode
dnaMacMoveMode.description: This object controls whether to allow authenticated hosts to do roaming across different switch ports. deny : When a host is authenticated on one port, that address is not allowed to move on another authenticated manager-enabled port of the device. permit: Authenticated hosts are allowed to move from one port to another on the same device. When a host moves to a new port, the authenticated session on the original port is deleted, and the host is re-authenticated on the new port.

dnaAuthorizationEnabled.name: dnaAuthorizationEnabled
dnaAuthorizationEnabled.description: This object indicates the state of acceptance of the authorized configuration. When authorization is enabled for authentication, the authorized attributes (for example VLAN, 802.1p default priority, bandwidth, and ACL) will be accepted.

dnaMacFormatCase.name: dnaMacFormatCase
dnaMacFormatCase.description: This object indicates the format of the authentication MAC address. uppercase: Using uppercase format, the formatted is: AA-BB-CC-DD-EE-FF. lowercase: Using lowercase format, the formatted is: aa-bb-cc-dd-ee-ff.

dnaMacFormatDelimiter.name: dnaMacFormatDelimiter
dnaMacFormatDelimiter.description: This object indicates the delimiter format of authentication MAC address. none: Not using any delimiter, the format is: AABBCCDDEEFF hyphen: Using '-' as delimiter, the format is: AA-BB-CC-DD-EE-FF colon: Using ':' as delimiter, the format is: AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF dot: Using '.' as delimiter, the format is: AA.BB.CC.DD.EE.FF

dnaMacFormatDelimiterNumber.name: dnaMacFormatDelimiterNumber
dnaMacFormatDelimiterNumber.description: This object indicates the delimiter number of authentication MAC address. 1: single delimiter, the format is: AABBCC.DDEEFF 2: double delimiter, the format is: AABB.CCDD.EEFF 5: multiple delimiter, the format is: AA.BB.CC.DD.EE.FF Note: while dnaMacFormatDelimiter is none(1), the delimiter number will not take effect.

dnaMaxAuthedUserLimit.name: dnaMaxAuthedUserLimit
dnaMaxAuthedUserLimit.description: This object indicates the maximum authenticated users of the system.

dnaPortConfigTable.name: dnaPortConfigTable
dnaPortConfigTable.description: This table is a list of configurations for ports. An entry will exist for every interface which supports Network Access Authentication feature.

dnaPortConfigEntry.name: dnaPortConfigEntry
dnaPortConfigEntry.description: An entry contains port-specific configuration for Network Access Authentication.

dnaPortMaxAuthedUserLimit.name: dnaPortMaxAuthedUserLimit
dnaPortMaxAuthedUserLimit.description: This object indicates the maximum authenticated users of this port.

dnaPortAuthHostMode.name: dnaPortAuthHostMode
dnaPortAuthHostMode.description: This object indicates the authentication host mode of the entry.

dnaPortAuthVlansFirst2K.name: dnaPortAuthVlansFirst2K
dnaPortAuthVlansFirst2K.description: This object specifies the authentication VLAN(s) in a string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 1 to 2048. If the bit is set to '1', then the VLAN needs authentication.

dnaPortAuthVlansSecond2K.name: dnaPortAuthVlansSecond2K
dnaPortAuthVlansSecond2K.description: This object specifies the authentication VLAN(s) in a string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 2049 to 4094. If the bit is set to '1', then the VLAN needs authentication.

dnaPortReauthEnabled.name: dnaPortReauthEnabled
dnaPortReauthEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the periodic re-authentication is enabled.

dnaPortReauthInterval.name: dnaPortReauthInterval
dnaPortReauthInterval.description: Specifies the re-authentication interval, after which the port will be re-authenticated if value of the corresponding instance of dnaPortReauthEnabled is 'true'. A value of zero indicates that the re-authentication interval is based on AAA server when this port is authenticated. Besides, the action (re-authenticate or initialize) to take after expiration of the timer is also based on server.

dnaPortRestartInterval.name: dnaPortRestartInterval
dnaPortRestartInterval.description: Specifies the interval after which a further authentication attempt should be made to this port if it is not authorized.

dnaPortInactivityTimeout.name: dnaPortInactivityTimeout
dnaPortInactivityTimeout.description: Specifies the period of time that a client associating with this port is allowed to be inactive before being terminated. A value of zero indicates that inactivity timeout is disabled on this port. A value of -1 indicates that inactivity timeout is based on AAA server when this port is authenticated.

dnaPortGuestVlanid.name: dnaPortGuestVlanid
dnaPortGuestVlanid.description: Specifies the VLAN ID of guest VLAN on the interface. The guest VLAN allows the user access within the guest VLAN before it is authenticated. A value of zero for this object indicates guest VLAN is not configured for the interface.

dnaPortMethodTable.name: dnaPortMethodTable
dnaPortMethodTable.description: The table contains a list of authentication methods information on ports. An entry will exist for every port which supports Network Access Authentication feature.

dnaPortMethodEntry.name: dnaPortMethodEntry
dnaPortMethodEntry.description: An entry contains configuration and information of authentication methods for a particular port.

dnaPortMethodAvailable.name: dnaPortMethodAvailable
dnaPortMethodAvailable.description: This object indicates the currently effective authentication methods on the port. e.g: The dnaPortMethodCompAuthMode of the interface is set to any(1), but only dot1x is running on this interface, macAuth, webAuth and jwac are disabled, only the bit of dot1x is '1'.

dnaPortMethodCompAuthMode.name: dnaPortMethodCompAuthMode
dnaPortMethodCompAuthMode.description: This object indicates the compound authentication mode on the port.

dnaSessionTable.name: dnaSessionTable
dnaSessionTable.description: The table contains a list of authentication sessions. An entry is created when an authentication session has been successfully created within Network Access Authentication. An entry is deleted when an authentication session has been removed.

dnaSessionEntry.name: dnaSessionEntry
dnaSessionEntry.description: An entry contains management information for a particular authentication session.

dnaSessionId.name: dnaSessionId
dnaSessionId.description: This object indicates a unique identifier of the authentication session.

dnaSessionClientMacAddress.name: dnaSessionClientMacAddress
dnaSessionClientMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the device associates with the authentication session.

dnaSessionClientAddrType.name: dnaSessionClientAddrType
dnaSessionClientAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of Internet address of the client associates with the authentication session. This object is meaningful only when the corresponding dnaSessionAuthorizedBy is webAuth or jwac.

dnaSessionClientAddress.name: dnaSessionClientAddress
dnaSessionClientAddress.description: This object indicates the Internet address of the client associates with the authentication session. This object is meaningful only when the corresponding dnaSessionAuthorizedBy is webAuth or jwac.

dnaSessionStatus.name: dnaSessionStatus
dnaSessionStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of the authentication session. idle : the session has been initialized and no method has run yet. authenticating : an authentication method is running for this session. noMethod : no authentication method has provided a result for this session. authenticationSuccess: an authentication method has resulted in authentication success for this session. authenticationFailed: an authentication method has resulted in authentication failed for this session.

dnaSessionAuthUserName.name: dnaSessionAuthUserName
dnaSessionAuthUserName.description: This object indicates the user name of the authentication session. This object is meaningless when the corresponding dnaSessionAuthorizedBy is macAuth and a zero length string will be returned.

dnaSessionAuthorizedBy.name: dnaSessionAuthorizedBy
dnaSessionAuthorizedBy.description: This object indicates the method which authorizes the authentication session.

dnaSessionAuthVlan.name: dnaSessionAuthVlan
dnaSessionAuthVlan.description: This object indicates the authorized VLAN applied to the authentication session. Value zero indicates that no authorized VLAN has been applied, or it is not applicable.

dnaSessionAccountingID.name: dnaSessionAccountingID
dnaSessionAccountingID.description: This object indicates the accounting session ID that using to accounting after authenticated.

dnaSessionAssignVid.name: dnaSessionAssignVid
dnaSessionAssignVid.description: This object indicates the effectively assigned VLAN ID that are authorized after host pass authenticated. A value of zero indicates that no valid VLAN ID is authorized.

dnaSessionAssignPriority.name: dnaSessionAssignPriority
dnaSessionAssignPriority.description: This object indicates the effectively assigned priority that is authorized after host pass authenticated. A value of -1 indicates that no valid priority is authorized.

dnaSessionAssignIngressBandwidth.name: dnaSessionAssignIngressBandwidth
dnaSessionAssignIngressBandwidth.description: This object indicates the effectively assigned ingress bandwidth that is authorized after host pass authenticated. A value of -1 indicates that no valid ingress is authorized.

dnaSessionAssignEgressBandwidth.name: dnaSessionAssignEgressBandwidth
dnaSessionAssignEgressBandwidth.description: This object indicates the effectively assigned egress bandwidth that is authorized after host pass authenticated. A value of -1 indicates that no valid egress is authorized.

dnaSessionTimeout.name: dnaSessionTimeout
dnaSessionTimeout.description: Indicates the session timeout used by Network Access Authentication for the authentication session.

dnaSessionTimeLeft.name: dnaSessionTimeLeft
dnaSessionTimeLeft.description: Indicates the leftover time of the authentication session.

dnaSessionInactivityTimeout.name: dnaSessionInactivityTimeout
dnaSessionInactivityTimeout.description: Indicates the inactivity timeout used by Network Access Authentication for the authentication session.

dnaSessionInactivityTimeLeft.name: dnaSessionInactivityTimeLeft
dnaSessionInactivityTimeLeft.description: Indicates the leftover time of the inactivity timer of the authentication session.

dnaSessionTerminateSession.name: dnaSessionTerminateSession
dnaSessionTerminateSession.description: This object terminates the authentication session, when set to 'terminate'. Setting this object to 'false' has no effect. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dnaSessionMethodInfoTable.name: dnaSessionMethodInfoTable
dnaSessionMethodInfoTable.description: The table contains a list of authenticating state information of methods for every authentication session. An entry exists for every authentication method that can initiate the authentication session within Network Access Authentication.

dnaSessionMethodInfoEntry.name: dnaSessionMethodInfoEntry
dnaSessionMethodInfoEntry.description: An entry contains information for a particular effective authentication method which is associated with a session on an interface.

dnaSessionMethod.name: dnaSessionMethod
dnaSessionMethod.description: Indicates the authentication method of the entry.

dnaSessionMethodState.name: dnaSessionMethodState
dnaSessionMethodState.description: Indicates the state of this authentication method. notInitiated : The method hasn't initiated the authentication process yet. inProgress : The authentication method is in progress. authcSuccess: The session has been authenticated by the method. authcFailed : The session has failed to be authenticated by the method.

dnaSessionTerminateIfTable.name: dnaSessionTerminateIfTable
dnaSessionTerminateIfTable.description: The table is used to terminate authentication sessions by interface.

dnaSessionTerminateIfEntry.name: dnaSessionTerminateIfEntry
dnaSessionTerminateIfEntry.description: An entry is used to terminate authentication sessions by specifying authentication methods per Network Access Authentication managed port.

dnaSessionTerminateIfMethodList.name: dnaSessionTerminateIfMethodList
dnaSessionTerminateIfMethodList.description: This object is used to terminate authentication sessions by methods on an interface by setting the corresponding bit to '1'. This object always returns '00'H when read.

dnaSessionTerminateMethod.name: dnaSessionTerminateMethod
dnaSessionTerminateMethod.description: This object is used to terminate the authentication sessions by setting this object to valid value. Setting this object to 'other' has no effect. When read, the value 'other' is returned.

dnaSessionTerminateAll.name: dnaSessionTerminateAll
dnaSessionTerminateAll.description: This object is used to terminate all authentication sessions by setting this object to 'terminateAll'. Setting this object to 'noOp' has no effect. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dnaUserTable.name: dnaUserTable
dnaUserTable.description: A table contains a list of users in the local database for authentication.

dnaUserEntry.name: dnaUserEntry
dnaUserEntry.description: An entry consists of information for an account.

dnaUserName.name: dnaUserName
dnaUserName.description: This object indicates the username for this user account.

dnaUserPassword.name: dnaUserPassword
dnaUserPassword.description: This object indicates the password in clear text form for this user account. When read, a zero length string will be returned for security reasons.

dnaUserTargetVlanid.name: dnaUserTargetVlanid
dnaUserTargetVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID to be assigned for this user account.

dnaUserRowStatus.name: dnaUserRowStatus
dnaUserRowStatus.description: This object manages this user account.

dnaCompliance.name: dnaCompliance
dnaCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement DLINKSW-NETWORK-ACCESS-MIB.

dnaAuthPortConfigGroup.name: dnaAuthPortConfigGroup
dnaAuthPortConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects that provides port-specific configuration of Network Access Authentication.

dnaPortMethodGroup.name: dnaPortMethodGroup
dnaPortMethodGroup.description: A collection of objects provides authentication methods configuration for Network Access Authentication.

dnaSessionGroup.name: dnaSessionGroup
dnaSessionGroup.description: A collection of objects that provides authentication session management information for Network Access Authentication.

dnaSessionMethodInfoGroup.name: dnaSessionMethodInfoGroup
dnaSessionMethodInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects that provides authentication session state information per authentication methods.

dnaMacMoveConfigGroup.name: dnaMacMoveConfigGroup
dnaMacMoveConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing MAC move configuration for Network Access Authentication on the device.

dnaAuthzConfigGroup.name: dnaAuthzConfigGroup
dnaAuthzConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects provides authorization configuration for Network Access Authentication on the device.

dnaMacFormatGroup.name: dnaMacFormatGroup
dnaMacFormatGroup.description: A collection of objects provides MAC format configuration for Network Access Authentication on the device.

dnaMaxAuthedUserLimitGroup.name: dnaMaxAuthedUserLimitGroup
dnaMaxAuthedUserLimitGroup.description: A collection of objects provides configuration of upper limits for authenticated user.

dnaGuestVlanGroup.name: dnaGuestVlanGroup
dnaGuestVlanGroup.description: A collection of objects providing guest VLAN configuration for Network Access Authentication on the device.

dnaAuthenticationVlanGroup.name: dnaAuthenticationVlanGroup
dnaAuthenticationVlanGroup.description: A collection of objects provides for the platform which supports the feature of per VLAN authentication.

dnaSessionTerminateGroup.name: dnaSessionTerminateGroup
dnaSessionTerminateGroup.description: A collection of objects providing terminate authentication session information for Network Access Authentication on the device.

dnaAccountUserGroup.name: dnaAccountUserGroup
dnaAccountUserGroup.description: A collection of objects providing local account information for Network Access Authentication on the device.
